download colmap binary for windows:
https://github.com/colmap/colmap/releases
(cuda if you have nvidia gpu, otherwise no cuda)

extract to downloads, and KEEP in downloads, otherwise change following paths accordingly (DEFAULT_COLMAP_PATHS in prepare_colmap_windows.py and the path for the colmap gui command you run in cmd/powershell):

run:
python prepare_colmap_windows.py <input_folder> <output_folder> --overwrite --export-ply

open cmd/powershell and run:
"C:\Users\login\Downloads\colmap-x64-windows-cuda\COLMAP.bat" gui

copy the path to your output file

go File > Import model > go to your output file > sparse > 0 
and then select
